oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mack Vickery Live at the Blue Denim House
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording is of Mick Vickery (musician) live at the Blue Denim House (unconfirmed). Vickery is accompanied by his band and Frank Denny (comedian). The recording is from an unidentified date.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Mack Vickery; Frank Denny
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:00k) Frank Denny inquires about people's knowledge of the "Haunted House" -- (00:41) Haunted House (Mack Vickery) -- (03:40) Denny jokes about being a Fuddpucker; additionally, Denny jokes around about being in school with his band -- (08:34) My Girlfriend Lives Over the Border (But Last Night She Came Across) (Mack Vickery) -- (15:15) Big Bruce (Mack Vickery) -- (19:36) Denny recalls a gentleman without any limbs; additionally, Denny and Vickery continues to make jokes about touring the south -- (31:41) Baltimore (Mick Vickery)
